== What happens on the short sits


During the short sessions that are recommended to repeat often. And what does often mean? I would say at least twice a day. What's happening there is well, let's say this is mala is my nervous system, my emotions, my thoughts. Well, generally we're picking at it and we're doing stuff with it---we're not letting it settle. 

So when we do the 10 minutes, anything that is... anything at all, anything felt, anything that's here, instead of getting involved with that, we're letting it settle. And then when we get up from the session, we'll have that much removal from grasping from that. Or they also call it cognitive fusion if you want to use fancy words.

So that cognitive diffusion is taking place during the 10 minute sessions. Yeah. But when you adjust to that then you you can get up and get a drink of water without any of that fusion. In fact there can be cognitive diffusion taking place as you're getting up and getting to water. Particularly if the view---if spaciousness and pure presence are invited into your life, when they're dawning into your life more---then there's this kind of revelation. 

And so you become like this spectrometer or this kind of measuring device. You know when there are fluctuations in your system: lots of thoughts, little thoughts, heavy emotions, light emotions, they're all on a kind of spectrum like a rainbow. Maybe you have blue emotions, green emotions, yellow emotions, blue thoughts, yellow thoughts. So that's the wonder of this practice is that sematically we can tune in to weight within space like presence. 

And there may be times before you get used to the view, before you reorientate into your wholeness, there may be times where you just... you're stuck on a thought or you're stuck on an emotion. And you turn awareness in on that. Right as you're speaking to yourself, or right as a feeling is coming up, a familiar feeling like anger or something like that. And there could very likely be tremors left over from that in the system. 

Sort of hurt... things that need to vibrate out of our systems. When something wants to breathe like, "Oh, I'm not good enough." or something like that. When that wants to get out of our consciousness, we take a story and bandage it back in there. "I'm not good enough because of this and because of that." And so the "not good enough" stays in our consciousness. But if "I'm not good enough" can just be a bird that flies through and leaves... okay, what's next? 

So yeah, I think main point here is that if you can manage to just let yourself be for 5 to 10 minutes and it's like this Longchenpa quote: "Let whatever happens happen and whatever manifests manifest. Let whatever occurs occur and whatever is be. Let whatever is anything at all be nothing at all".

